news.title: Bombay HC slaps contempt show-cause notice on doctor who suppressed facts to claim SRA tenement
news.para: Bombay High Court issued a contempt notice to a doctor for suppressing facts while claiming a rehabilitation tenement. The court found she illegally occupied over 2,200 sq ft and used structures as residence, clinic, and school, dismissing her petition with Rs 5 lakh costs. Authorities were directed to re-examine slum scheme verification processes.

news.title: Ahmedabad’s biggest land deal sets stamp duty record of ₹31 crore
news.para: Ahmedabad witnessed its largest land deal as LuLu International Shopping Malls Pvt Ltd acquired a 66,168 sq m plot in Chandkheda for Rs 519.41 crore. This landmark transaction generated a record Rs 31 crore in stamp duty for the government.

news.title: HC summons Uttarkashi DM over illegal construction in eco-sensitive zone
news.para: The Uttarakhand High Court has taken a firm stance, summoning officials from Uttarkashi district in response to a petition that raises alarms over unauthorized hotel and resort projects in the Bhagirathi Eco-Sensitive Zone. These constructions purportedly breach regulations set by the National Green Tribunal, prompting the court to request a detailed compliance report.

news.title: Encroachment of lands acquired for Rajasthan Housing Board 'absolute rank scam': SC
news.para: The Supreme Court has declared the encroachment of land acquired for the Rajasthan Housing Board a major scam. JThe court criticized attempts to regularize illegal constructions on housing board land. The Rajasthan government was allowed to withdraw its plea and approach the High Court for relief.

news.title: DDA to open flat registrations for 48-storey high rise residential society in East Delhi
news.para: Registration is now open for DDA's new residential project, DDA Towering Heights. This 48-storey building in Karkardooma offers 1,026 premium two-bedroom-hall-kitchen apartments. Prices range from Rs 1.78 crore to Rs 3.09 crore. The project is set for handover by July 2026. It boasts excellent connectivity and is part of a major urban development.

news.title: India Cements logs profit of ₹8.81 crore in Q2 FY26; to invest ₹2,014 crore on expansion
news.para: India Cements Ltd, now part of Aditya Birla Group, posted a net profit of Rs 8.81 crore for the September quarter of FY26. The company's board approved a significant Rs 2,014 crore investment. This includes Rs 1,574 crore for modernization and Rs 440 crore for capacity expansion. Revenue from operations saw a 9.31 percent increase.

news.title: UT chief secretary reviews functioning of Chandigarh housing board
news.para: Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) reviewed operational efficiency and accountability under UT Chief Secretary H Rajesh Prasad. The board was directed to develop innovative housing schemes, boost public awareness for Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) 2.0, and install solar panels on CHB flats to align with the city's development and solar city vision.

news.title: Sobha posts net profit of ₹72.52 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Sobha has announced strong financial results for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. The company's net profit after tax surged to ₹72.52 crore. Total income also saw a substantial rise of 52.22 percent. Sobha's managing director expressed confidence in future growth, citing a robust pipeline and stable demand.

news.title: Polycab India's consolidated net profit up 55.64% at ₹692.95 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Polycab India's net profit surged by 55.64 percent year-on-year to Rs 692.95 crore in Q2 FY26. Revenue from operations also saw a significant increase of 17.80 percent, reaching Rs 6,477.21 crore. This performance highlights the robust growth in both the wires and cables and FMEG businesses.

news.title: Rajasthan may allow land conversion near Jawai leopard reserve
news.para: Rajasthan government is considering allowing land conversion within the 1km Eco-Sensitive Zone of Jawai Bandh leopard conservation area. This move, prompted by a hotelier's representation, could impact conservation efforts and wildlife, despite arguments that it would boost local livelihoods and economic opportunities.

news.title: HooLiv raises ₹24 crore in pre-series A round
news.para: HooLiv, a co-living and student housing platform, has secured ₹24 crore in a new funding round. The investment will fuel expansion into non-metro cities. This includes acquiring more beds and enhancing its property management platform. The company anticipates significant growth and changes in the student housing sector.

news.title: M3M India to invest ₹2,100 crore in Jacob & Co. Residences, Noida
news.para: M3M India is investing ₹2,100 crore to launch Jacob & Co. Residences in Noida's central business district, marking the brand's India debut. The project, spanning six acres, will feature 250 ultra-luxury residences across two phases, with prices ranging from ₹14 crore to ₹25 crore. Completion is targeted within three years.

news.title: Arkade Developers's profit up 6% to ₹45.8 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Arkade Developers' net profit rose by 6 per cent to Rs 45.80 crore for the September quarter. This growth was driven by higher revenue. Total income also saw a significant jump. Arkade Developers has a strong track record of property delivery and ongoing projects.

news.title: Kalpataru's sales bookings up 19% to ₹1,329 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Kalpataru Ltd has reported substantial financial growth, showcasing a 19% rise in sales bookings to Rs 1,329 crore during the second quarter of the fiscal year. This upswing signifies a notable increase in housing interest.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's profit rises 41% to ₹48.96 crore in Q2 FY26
news.para: Sunteck Realty has announced a significant 41 percent jump in its consolidated net profit for the second quarter of this fiscal year. The company's net profit reached Rs 48.96 crore, a notable rise from Rs 34.62 crore in the same period last year. This impressive growth was driven by a substantial increase in total income, which climbed to Rs 262.

news.title: Sub-registrars can deny registration of house sites: Madras HC
news.para: Sub-registrars can now refuse to register plots as house sites without planning authority approval, the Madras High Court clarified. A division bench allowed an appeal by a sub-registrar, reversing a single judge's order. The court emphasized that land converted to a house site requires prior approval unless previously registered as such, upholding the Registration Act's Section 22 A.

news.title: Technical team inspects Maradu flats’ site
news.para: A technical team from the Kerala Coastal Zone Management Authority inspected the Maradu demolition sites following a Supreme Court directive. The inspection focused on assessing CRZ violations, nearby water bodies, and land restoration efforts. A detailed report on post-demolition environmental restoration will be submitted to the central and state governments.

news.title: MahaRERA clears record 200 registrations in a day, 809 projects in fortnight
news.para: MahaRERA approved a record 200 housing projects in a single day and 809 applications in two weeks, including new registrations, extensions, and corrections. This surge in clearances, particularly in Pune and MMR, reflects ongoing housing demand and developers' efforts to meet buyer interest while ensuring regulatory compliance.

news.title: Parking space mandate relaxed for new large homes in Tamil Nadu; usable FSI set to rise
news.para: Tamil Nadu has amended its building rules, reducing parking requirements for new large residential buildings. Houses on plots of 3,200 sqft or more now need space for four cars and four two-wheelers, down from previous mandates. This change aims to increase usable construction area, though urban planners caution it may exacerbate on-street parking issues.

news.title: Deputy CM transfers ₹17.7 crore unpaid rent to 883 families of Magathane SRA project in Mumbai
news.para: Deputy Chief Minister Eknath Shinde transferred Rs 17.7 crore in pending rent to 883 slum families in Magathane, a move seen as appeasing voters ahead of BMC polls. This action addresses a long-stalled SRA project, with the total owed rent reaching Rs 46 crore. The SRA is implementing policy reforms to ensure slum dwellers receive their dues promptly.
